246
00:11:22,598 --> 00:11:25,598
My husband won't have
any problem not drinking.

247
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:27,055
Yeah...

248
00:11:27,144 --> 00:11:29,064
The only reason he wanted
to become Duffman

249
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:31,106
was to be respected and beloved.

250
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:32,570
Uh...

251
00:11:32,650 --> 00:11:36,650
And what better way to do that
than to be stone-cold sober?

252
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:37,947
(moans)

253
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:39,950
When my husband
put on that costume,

254
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:41,952
he didn't just
put on a sleeveless shirt

255
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:45,714
that says "Duff" on it
and a cape for some reason,

256
00:11:45,788 --> 00:11:47,498
he put on responsibility.

257
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:51,041
And boots that I don't think
will hold up in the rain.

258
00:11:51,127 --> 00:11:53,877
But the point is--
it's not about being drunk,

259
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:56,553
it's about being someone.

260
00:11:56,632 --> 00:11:58,552
You're right, Marge.

261
00:11:58,634 --> 00:12:03,104
I will do something no one has
ever done-- be fun sober.

262
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:05,890
What a crisp
and refreshing attitude.

263
00:12:08,227 --> 00:12:10,897
Hey, this stuff is pretty good.

264
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:16,694
Mmm, foamy Marge.

265
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:18,987
(babbling)

266
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:21,405
Uh, that's the chip.

267
00:12:21,490 --> 00:12:22,580
No drinking.

268
00:12:22,658 --> 00:12:25,408
I was licking my wife.

269
00:12:25,494 --> 00:12:28,414
Can you believe they
put a chip in my arm,

270
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:29,707
and I can't drink beer?

271
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,920
-Ah.
-Ah, gee, tough break.

272
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:34,131
Maybe Moe could dig it out
with a corkscrew.

273
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:35,211
Yeah.

274
00:12:35,296 --> 00:12:37,126
Oh, I would love that,
Homer, I really would.

275
00:12:37,214 --> 00:12:39,684
But then Duff might take away
my neon sign,

276
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:42,139
and, uh, it's the only thing
lighting the bar.

277
00:12:42,219 --> 00:12:43,929
BARNEY:
Whoa, creepy.

278
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:47,354
(Bart and Lisa laugh
mischievously)

279
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:50,023
Stop shooting those at each other.

280
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:53,482
Relax, honey, no one's ever
been killed by a T-shirt cannon.

281
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:05,534
Oh, no, it's the 5:00 blahs.

282
00:13:05,618 --> 00:13:08,538
CLOCKS:
Blah, blah, blah, blah.

283
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:10,961
Help us, Duffman!

284
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,120
(laughs heroically)

285
00:13:12,208 --> 00:13:13,128
(screams)

286
00:13:13,209 --> 00:13:15,169
Drink Duff!

287
00:13:15,252 --> 00:13:17,052
(crowd cheers)

288
00:13:17,129 --> 00:13:18,879
Care to team up with Fruit Batman?

289
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:22,134
I'm thinking of dumping
Kid Sourpuss here.

290
00:13:22,218 --> 00:13:26,138
I'm a hero.
Oh, I can see my obituary now.

291
00:13:27,431 --> 00:13:29,641
Wow. Wow!

292
00:13:29,725 --> 00:13:32,895
{\an8}<i>COMMENTATOR: Watkins putting</i>
<i>for the championship.</i>

293
00:13:32,978 --> 00:13:36,188
{\an8}<i>It's breaking towards the hole.</i>

294
00:13:36,273 --> 00:13:39,693
Time to move from the links
to the drinks!

295
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:41,487
(cheering)

296
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:44,320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

297
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,290
Well, if you guys like commercials,

298
00:13:53,374 --> 00:13:54,834
you're gonna love this.

299
00:13:54,917 --> 00:13:57,417
Wait, we never said
we liked commercials.

300
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:59,173
<i>♪ Drink, drink ♪</i>

301
00:13:59,255 --> 00:14:01,005
<i>♪ Let the toast start ♪</i>

302
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:03,760
<i>♪ May young hearts never part ♪</i>

303
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:05,513
<i>♪ Drink, drink, drink ♪</i>

304
00:14:05,594 --> 00:14:10,104
<i>♪ Let every true lover</i>
<i>salute his sweetheart... ♪</i>

305
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:12,522
{\an8}♪ <i>Drink, drink, drink to...</i> ♪

306
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:17,768
H.K., this new Duffman
is driving sales straight up.

307
00:14:17,857 --> 00:14:20,187
Turns out, men like men
who look worse than them

308
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:21,606
selling them beer.

309
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:25,284
Why did it take us 142 years
to discover this?

310
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,954
Because executives are
incompetent, sir?

311
00:14:28,033 --> 00:14:29,873
Well, then why do I have so many?

312
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:32,622
Studies show when a decision
is made by a group,

313
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:34,285
everyone feels more confident,

314
00:14:34,373 --> 00:14:36,833
even though the decision
could be incredibly stupid.

315
00:14:36,917 --> 00:14:39,337
-Is this true?
-(affirming)

316
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:41,710
Can't argue with that.
What do you guys think?

317
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:43,507
(affirming)

318
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:46,221
Did I hear a no
from section C-72?

319
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:49,102
Oh, uh, no,
that was a, uh, "whoa!"

320
00:14:49,179 --> 00:14:50,429
(chuckling)
Oh.

321
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:52,984
Give the whole
lower bowl a raise.

322
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:56,516
Uh, welcome aboard, Duffman.

323
00:14:56,604 --> 00:14:58,484
Fair warning now-- at the end,

324
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:01,574
I just might ask
for an autograph for my son.

325
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:04,240
Here you go-- they're all pre-signed.
With nicknames.

326
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:06,570
Buddy, Sport, Tiger, Red.

327
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:08,315
Uh, give me a "Red."

328
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:09,617
I'll start calling him that now,

329
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:11,830
and then give it to him
on his birthday.

330
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:13,831
Now, where to, sir?

331
00:15:13,913 --> 00:15:15,373
Oh, this is a romantic night.

332
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:17,076
How about everywhere?

333
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:18,246
All right.

334
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:20,924
Navigator,
set a course for everywhere.

335
00:15:21,003 --> 00:15:22,093
Where the hell is that?

336
00:15:22,171 --> 00:15:23,671
I said everywhere!

337
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:27,380
Now, Homer,
look through the beeriscope,

338
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:29,388
and gaze upon the wonderful world

339
00:15:29,470 --> 00:15:32,010
that you and Duff have created.

340
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:50,031
Captain, it never dawned on me

341
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:52,405
beer could have such a dark side.

342
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:54,833
You must be talking about
new Duff Stout.

343
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:55,872
Take us down.

344
00:15:55,955 --> 00:15:57,365
I have to think.

345
00:15:57,456 --> 00:16:00,166
To be honest, you said
you wanted to go everywhere.

346
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:02,540
So we ran out of fuel
an hour ago,

347
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,798
but I didn't want
to disappoint you,

348
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:07,340
so I will toss down a tow rope.

349
00:16:09,885 --> 00:16:12,755
Hey, come here. Man...

350
00:16:15,015 --> 00:16:17,595
Uh... this is not good.

351
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:23,361
(sighs)
Marge, do you ever worry

352
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:26,190
that you made
a giant mistake in your life?

353
00:16:26,276 --> 00:16:28,236
Oh, um...

354
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,950
I need a little context.

355
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:33,120
Not drinking beer has given me
the clearness of mind

356
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:36,120
to realize drinking beer is bad.

357
00:16:36,203 --> 00:16:38,043
I've got to undo what I've done.

358
00:16:38,122 --> 00:16:40,212
Hey, how you doing?

359
00:16:42,292 --> 00:16:44,382
(dance music playing)

360
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:48,171
Is this the most outrageous party
you've ever been to?

361
00:16:48,257 --> 00:16:50,047
(cheering, affirming)

362
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:51,554
Well, guess what.

363
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:55,425
You've all been served nothing
but nonalcoholic Duff.

364
00:16:55,514 --> 00:16:56,894
(spectators gasping)

365
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:59,734
BARNEY:
Then why am I throwing up right now?

366
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:01,400
As Duffman, I had the power

367
00:17:01,478 --> 00:17:04,398
<i>to switch the beer trucks</i>
<i>working this race.</i>

368
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:11,241
(screams)

369
00:17:11,321 --> 00:17:14,831
So you see, you don't need beer
to have a good time.

370
00:17:14,908 --> 00:17:17,488
Join Duffman today in saying,

371
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:21,668
"I've had enough
of that life-ruining Duff!"

372
00:17:21,749 --> 00:17:23,669
Why the hell did you do this?

373
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:25,171
Because Duffman is a hero.

374
00:17:25,252 --> 00:17:28,052
And with great taste
comes great responsibility.

375
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:31,010
Well, "hero," here come your fans.

376
00:17:31,091 --> 00:17:32,511
(shouting indistinctly)

377
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:33,973
(yelps)

378
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:36,183
-(engine starts)
-So long, suckers!

379
00:17:36,263 --> 00:17:37,513
(laughing maniacally)

380
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:43,649
What the...?!

381
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:45,059
So long, suckers!

382
00:17:45,147 --> 00:17:47,897
(Homer laughing maniacally)

383
00:17:47,983 --> 00:17:49,113
What the...?!

384
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:50,283
It's a circle.

385
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,700
So the answer is--
go in reverse.

386
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:54,070
So long, suckers.

387
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:55,526
(Homer laughing maniacally)

388
00:17:55,616 --> 00:17:56,656
What the...?!

389
00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:58,412
I'm not sure
how many more times

390
00:17:58,494 --> 00:18:01,504
we can watch Dad chased down
by an angry crowd

391
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:03,290
before it affects us psychologically.

392
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:05,293
As a family therapist,
I can assure you

393
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:07,835
that you have
all the coping skills you need.

394
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:09,920
Why is Lisa talking to an empty seat?

395
00:18:10,005 --> 00:18:11,915
See you next Tuesday, Dr. Schulman.

396
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:14,837
Oh, right.
You're in Maui.

397
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:15,927
(whimpers)

398
00:18:16,011 --> 00:18:17,431
Hey, my beer.

399
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:18,433
(screams)

400
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:21,484
(panting frantically)

401
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:23,848
(gargling)

402
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:25,646
Get him back in uniform.

403
00:18:27,272 --> 00:18:29,112
Hmm.

404
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:30,321
Homer, now, listen to me.

405
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,860
You're in a stadium
surrounded by people

406
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,355
who want to kill you.

407
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:36,696
They don't have the guts.

408
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:37,872
Ow.

409
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:40,160
Now, there's one way
out of your hell.

410
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:42,704
Prove you still love beer.

411
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,788
Drink this with gusto.

412
00:18:44,873 --> 00:18:46,293
B-But the chip.

413
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:47,705
There never was a chip.

414
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,883
It was all the power of suggestion.

415
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:51,172
You tricked me!

416
00:18:51,255 --> 00:18:53,505
And I trusted you
after you snuck up

417
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:56,220
and injected me
without my consent.

418
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:58,551
Just drink the beer, pretty boy.

419
00:18:58,637 --> 00:19:01,637
Whatever you do,
you'll be my hero.

420
00:19:03,016 --> 00:19:04,936
Now you're pushing it.

421
00:19:05,018 --> 00:19:08,768
Homie, it's time to go.

422
00:19:08,856 --> 00:19:10,106
Come on, come on.

423
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:12,990
Give me the beer inside you!

424
00:19:13,068 --> 00:19:14,398
Oi.

425
00:19:15,821 --> 00:19:18,491
This place seems
even sadder than before.

426
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:20,704
Uh, yeah, well,
I kind of gloomed it up a little

427
00:19:20,784 --> 00:19:21,794
while you were gone.

428
00:19:22,953 --> 00:19:25,163
Nothing to see here, sunshine.

429
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:26,327
(sighs)

430
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:29,325
(slurring)
H-Hey, y-you used to be Duffman.

431
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:31,248
Can I get a picture with you?

432
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,586
(gasps)
I finally made it.

433
00:19:33,672 --> 00:19:35,592
I'm a has-been.

434
00:19:35,674 --> 00:19:37,344
Yeah, I guess you're right.

435
00:19:37,426 --> 00:19:39,636
Ah, let's make it official, eh?

436
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:44,268
Aw...

437
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:50,611
Oh, yeah.

438
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:53,229
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

439
00:19:53,317 --> 00:19:55,777
Sir, may I interest you
in a French hazelnut latte

440
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:57,281
and an Iggy Azalea CD?

441
00:19:57,362 --> 00:19:59,782
I'm not here for three-buck coffee.

442
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:02,775
I'm here to ask you
to be Duffman again.

443
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:04,448
And to use the bathroom.

444
00:20:04,536 --> 00:20:06,156
I don't know what you're
talking about, sir.

445
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:09,036
Fine, can you tell me
where your travel mugs are?

446
00:20:09,124 --> 00:20:10,134
Yeah, over there.

447
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:13,089
Come on, Barry, I know it's you.

448
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:15,420
Sorry, H.K.,
I traded in my beer goggles

449
00:20:15,505 --> 00:20:17,505
for coffee-grinding pince-nez.

450
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:20,141
Are you telling me
you don't miss the big time?

451
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,849
The girls on the side,
the corporate jet?

452
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:25,520
There's talk of an animated series.

453
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:29,099
Duffman would like a job
where he could phone it in.

454
00:20:29,186 --> 00:20:31,436
You just called yourself Duffman.

455
00:20:31,521 --> 00:20:34,361
Duffman never took off his tights!

456
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:36,321
Let's go, girls!

457
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:38,111
But we're managers here.

458
00:20:38,195 --> 00:20:41,655
They learned the register
better than me! Oh, yeah!

459
00:21:27,119 --> 00:21:29,159
Oh, yeah!

460
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:34,960
Subtitled by Jimmy Boots

